      "content": "To distinguish between a tourist and a professional anywhere, prioritize \"global business standards\" like structured separates, dark-colored trousers, and minimalistic jewelry, which remain universally acceptable across Asia, Africa, and the Middle East regardless of local trends. When dining spoons and forks are always used even in regions where hands are traditional, and the tablecloth remains in place until the very end. Additionally, avoid carrying a phone in visible displays or sitting with your back to the group, as these small details can instantly make you look un observant or disrespectful. Sticking to these rigid, color-neutral guidelines creates an immediate silhouette of competence that transcends specific cultural expectations.",
